reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 8, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful, quiet, cool
reviews.reviewText: Love it.best under 25.00 cooler I have personally came across. Im using it for a Ryzen CPU. Easy to install. The RGB is BEAUTIFUL, Vivid and Bright!!! Just installed this last night, so the thermal paste is still "setting" . I have a good case and I use 4 case fans (3 front, 1 back) and my CPU is at 36-38 Celcius while Idle and while Gaming, I tested playing Cyberpunk 2077 at ultra Settings on a 1440 display and the CPU temp never went over 58 degrees celcius. Yeah, Im very happy. Its also a very warm summer day, so factor that in a bit too.Pros-Beautiful, addressable RGBEasy to instal (I used it for AMD Ryzen)Good instructionsQuiet!!! Very QuietGreat price.Comes with a tube of thermal paste ( I used my own though)Cons-It will not jump out of the box and install itself no matter how much you beg...Highly recommend. Its a capable and Gorgeous Cooler.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 9, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Keeps Ryzen 5 3600 Cool Runnings
reviews.reviewText: Upgraded the stock AMD Wraith cooler that my Ryzen 5 3600 came with and this bad boy gets the job done and then some.Installation was confusing at first, but that was due to user error. After I figured it out, installed in less than 5 minutes, connected it to my ASUS B550-M Plus mobo and it's quiet and effective.I was worried at first the fan might block the RAM slots on the motherboard but that hasn't been an issue. I can easily get RAM in and out of the slots near the fan.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Maybe, but will it clear your ram?
reviews.reviewText: It's big, beautiful, functional, an easy buy at $20 and the diffuse rgb it puts out is a perfect match for my Corsair vengeance pro rgb. it's wide and relatively low profile and even given that it wasn't that hard to install and comes with a packet of thermal paste. (It was the last thing i installed before the graphics card.) The only mark against it is that it's also very slightly wider then I expected. I am using 2 sticks in the fastest slots for this configuration but if I wanted to put matching RGB ram in the slot closest to the cpu it would be blocked.i think regular or low profile ram would fit, but my dreams of upping my ram past the 32gb I installed won't happen until I replace or modify this. This is why I took off one star. Why buy this if you don't care about RGB, and if you care about RGB you likely have taller RGB ram.Also, it's not a fault against the fan, but if looks and max rgb is your goal, this will make it harder to see an rgb m.2 ssd.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 13, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice air cooled fancy fan! Don’t hesitate.
reviews.reviewText: I needed to upgrade the heat sink, I was using a stock ASUS heat sink for an i5 for an i7 until I could grab an upgrade.Mounting the Thermaltake was a piece of cake, I have an LGA 1151 motherboard. It stands over the RAM slots that are occupied on mine, and doesn’t interfere with anything else. The bracket it comes with was easy! I just lined it up, put the pegs in place to hold it, and then applied the tiny push pins in. Once that happened and it was secured, I attached the fan with my thermal paste (it comes with thermal paste if you don’t have any), and clipped it in.Because of my small space I work with, I had to pull out the GPU to clip it in. But that was easy as pie as well.It took about five minutes or so to install it. Super simple! It’s VERY EASY! So if you aren’t savvy with computer parts, you seriously won’t have any trouble.I haven’t tested it on a game while streaming yet, but I notice at least a 10-15 degree drop in operation temperature from an app that I use.It’s VERY quiet, the fan is fancy, I love the color scheme it rotates, it’s absolutely beautiful! I’m glad I bought this!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Too loud, too difficult of an install but at least it looks nice.
reviews.reviewText: Pros: RGB, if you care for that, keeps your cpu cool if it's 65 watts or less, 120mm fan, Premium look to it, lightweight, price, fits both AMD and Intel mobos.Cons:3 pins, no pwm 4 pin connector, fan runs at 100%, install was a pain to get it to seat on the bracket, due to its size it will force you to remove a ram slot if you're using 4 ram sticks on your mobo, poor cable management.Alright, I'll keep this brief and I'll start with the negatives as there are plenty. First off, due to the 3 pin design the fan will run at 100% so if you value quiet and hate a lot of noise, avoid this one because it's loud, 1800 rpm's to be exact. The install was a pain, the clamps on both sides are too short forcing one to put a lot of pressure to seat the clamps onto the bracket and if you're not careful you can damage your mobo.Depending on the height of your ram you may be forced to remove one of them in order to get this thing to fit so keep this in mind when considering buying this. The cables for RGB and cpu fan headers cables can ruin a clean look as they long enough to reach the RGB headers on your mobo but not long enough to hide the wires.Just another note for those thinking of buying this for either Intel or AMD the bracket that comes with it must be used for Intel processors only but on AMD platforms just reuse the stock AMD brackets. Just putting that out there for those curious about the bracket.Final verdict, I'd avoid this as there just too many negatives for me to recommend it to anyone.
Me gusto este disipador lo ocupe para un ryzen 5 2600x,con el disipador de stock llegaba a los 85 grados jugando y con este llega a los 64 grados jugando,y no pasa los 70,lo recomiendo 100%

Okey, primero lo primero.Es un gran disipador. Y no me refiero sólo al trabajo que hace, porque ha mantenido fresco (unos 40°C) un procesador que con el disipador de stock se calentaba de más (unos 60°C). El ventilador hace muy poco ruido, la iluminación RGB es preciosa, y combina muy bien con la iluminación integrada de la tarjeta madre, PERO, porque siempre hay un pero, hay que tener cuidado con qué tarjeta madre lo instalas. A lo que me refiero es que es un procesador grande, ancho, pero chaparro, lo que es bueno cuando metes todo en un gabinete slim o low profile, pero es un problema con algunas tarjetas madre y algunas memorias. Específicamente, con las mías.Instalé este ventilador en una tarjeta Asus Prime A320M-K. Ojo a este dato, porque tiene razón de ser. Las memorias que le instalé a esta tarjeta madre son muy altas, como suele ser normal en las memorias que tienen RGB. Pues bien, la tarjeta madre tiene las ranuras de las memorias muy cerca del zócalo AM4, y el disipador es muy amplio, y el efecto secundario fue que si pongo una memoria en la ranura A no alcanza a entrar el disipador, forzándome a ponerlo en la ranura B, donde entra pero justo, casi tocando la memoria con la parte de plástico del ventilador RGB. Así que no puedo poner toda la memoria que quiero porque físicamente no cabe. Puedo intentar poner una memoria más baja, y probablemente tampoco entre. Para poder poner más memorias, los zócalos deben estar alejados del procesador. Así, una tarjeta madre MicroATX como ésta muy probablemente no sea la adecuada para este disipador.Fuera de ello, reitero, es un gran disipador. Definitivamente lo volveré a comprar.
